        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scratchpad Memory"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A scratchpad is a private, ephemeral writing space that an agent uses to reason before it produces a visible answer. It is not part of the conversation the user sees \u2014 it is where the agent thinks out loud, plans tool calls, records observations, and revises its approach. The scratchpad exists entirely inside the context buffer, usually in a structured block that the prompt instructs the model to fill before giving its final response."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Scratchpads Improve Agent Quality"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Large language models perform better when they are allowed to work through a problem incrementally rather than producing an answer in one pass. A scratchpad gives the model a place to:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Decompose a complex question into sub-questions before answering any of them."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Record intermediate tool results so they can be referenced in later reasoning steps."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Detect and correct errors mid-chain \u2014 if a search returns unexpected data, the model can note the discrepancy and replan."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Avoid premature commitment \u2014 writing out a plan before executing it catches logical gaps."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Chain-of-thought prompting is the minimal version of a scratchpad: one instruction ('Think step by step') that tells the model to reason before answering. Structured scratchpads add explicit fields and turn that into a controllable interface."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anatomy of a Scratchpad Turn"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Scratchpad memory \u2014 agent reasoning flow diagram",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each agent turn follows the same three-phase pattern: the model writes to the scratchpad (Thought), executes an action (Act), then records what it observed (Observe). This cycle repeats until the model decides it has enough information to produce the final answer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementing a Scratchpad with XML Tags"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The simplest scratchpad is a pair of XML-style delimiters that the prompt instructs the model to use. The application strips the scratchpad block before showing the response to the user."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nYou are a research assistant. Before answering, use a private scratchpad\nto plan your approach, record tool results, and reflect on what you learn.\n\nFormat your response as:\n<scratchpad>\nThought: ...\nPlan: ...\nObservation: ...     (fill in after each tool call)\nReflection: ...\n</scratchpad>\n<answer>\nYour final answer here.\n</answer>\n\"\"\".strip()\n\nimport re\n\ndef extract_answer(raw: str) -> tuple[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Split the raw model output into (scratchpad_text, answer_text).\n    Returns empty strings for missing sections.\n    \"\"\"\n    scratchpad = \"\"\n    answer = \"\"\n\n    sp_match = re.search(r\"<scratchpad>(.*?)</scratchpad>\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if sp_match:\n        scratchpad = sp_match.group(1).strip()\n\n    ans_match = re.search(r\"<answer>(.*?)</answer>\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if ans_match:\n        answer = ans_match.group(1).strip()\n    else:\n        # Fallback: everything after the scratchpad block\n        answer = re.sub(r\"<scratchpad>.*?</scratchpad>\", \"\", raw, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n\n    return scratchpad, answer\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Structured Scratchpad with Typed Fields"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For multi-step agents that call tools, a more structured format prevents the model from mixing reasoning with output. Each field has a defined purpose:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\n@dataclass\nclass ScratchpadEntry:\n    thought: str = \"\"       # What the model is thinking about\n    plan: str = \"\"          # Next action(s) to take\n    observation: str = \"\"   # Result of the most recent tool call\n    reflection: str = \"\"    # What the result means for the overall goal\n    partial_answer: str = \"\"  # Best answer so far, updated each step\n\n    def to_prompt_block(self) -> str:\n        lines = [\"<scratchpad>\"]\n        if self.thought:\n            lines.append(f\"Thought: {self.thought}\")\n        if self.plan:\n            lines.append(f\"Plan: {self.plan}\")\n        if self.observation:\n            lines.append(f\"Observation: {self.observation}\")\n        if self.reflection:\n            lines.append(f\"Reflection: {self.reflection}\")\n        if self.partial_answer:\n            lines.append(f\"Partial answer: {self.partial_answer}\")\n        lines.append(\"</scratchpad>\")\n        return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_text(cls, text: str) -> \"ScratchpadEntry\":\n        \"\"\"Parse a scratchpad block back into a structured object.\"\"\"\n        def extract(label: str) -> str:\n            m = re.search(rf\"{label}:\\s*(.*?)(?=\\n[A-Z][a-z]+:|</scratchpad>)\", text, re.DOTALL)\n            return m.group(1).strip() if m else \"\"\n\n        return cls(\n            thought=extract(\"Thought\"),\n            plan=extract(\"Plan\"),\n            observation=extract(\"Observation\"),\n            reflection=extract(\"Reflection\"),\n            partial_answer=extract(\"Partial answer\"),\n        )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ReAct: Scratchpad as a Loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ReAct pattern (Reason + Act) is the dominant framework for tool-using agents. The scratchpad implements the Reason step; a tool call implements the Act step; the tool result populates the Observation. The loop continues until the model produces a final answer instead of another tool call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\nimport json\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nTOOLS = [\n    {\n        \"name\": \"search\",\n        \"description\": \"Search the web for a query.\",\n        \"input_schema\": {\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\"query\": {\"type\": \"string\"}},\n            \"required\": [\"query\"],\n        },\n    }\n]\n\ndef fake_search(query: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Stand-in for a real search tool.\"\"\"\n    return f\"[Search results for '{query}': Revenue Q3 $2.4M, Q2 $2.1M, growth 12%]\"\n\ndef run_react_agent(user_question: str, max_steps: int = 8) -> str:\n    messages: list[dict] = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_question}]\n    scratchpads: list[str] = []\n\n    for step in range(max_steps):\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-sonnet-5\",\n            max_tokens=1024,\n            system=SYSTEM_PROMPT,\n            tools=TOOLS,\n            messages=messages,\n        )\n\n        # Collect any text (may include scratchpad block)\n        text_parts = [b.text for b in response.content if b.type == \"text\"]\n        raw_text = \"\\n\".join(text_parts)\n        if raw_text:\n            scratchpad, _ = extract_answer(raw_text)\n            if scratchpad:\n                scratchpads.append(f\"Step {step + 1}: {scratchpad}\")\n\n        # Check for tool use\n        tool_calls = [b for b in response.content if b.type == \"tool_use\"]\n        if not tool_calls:\n            # Model chose not to call a tool \u2014 extract the final answer\n            _, answer = extract_answer(raw_text)\n            return answer or raw_text\n\n        # Execute all tool calls and append results\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n        tool_results = []\n        for tc in tool_calls:\n            if tc.name == \"search\":\n                result = fake_search(tc.input[\"query\"])\n            else:\n                result = f\"Unknown tool: {tc.name}\"\n            tool_results.append({\n                \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n                \"tool_use_id\": tc.id,\n                \"content\": result,\n            })\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n\n    return \"Max steps reached without a final answer.\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Persisting Scratchpad Entries Across Turns"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "By default a scratchpad is cleared when a new user turn begins. For long sessions it can be useful to carry forward a condensed version \u2014 the key decisions and partial answers \u2014 so the model does not repeat work it already did."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@dataclass\nclass PersistentScratchpad:\n    entries: list[ScratchpadEntry] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n    def add(self, entry: ScratchpadEntry) -> None:\n        self.entries.append(entry)\n        # Keep only the last 5 entries to control token usage\n        if len(self.entries) > 5:\n            self.entries = self.entries[-5:]\n\n    def to_context_block(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Render the scratchpad history as a compact context injection.\"\"\"\n        if not self.entries:\n            return \"\"\n        lines = [\"[SCRATCHPAD HISTORY]\"]\n        for i, e in enumerate(self.entries, 1):\n            if e.partial_answer:\n                lines.append(f\"  Step {i} partial answer: {e.partial_answer}\")\n            if e.reflection:\n                lines.append(f\"  Step {i} reflection: {e.reflection}\")\n        return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n    def latest_partial_answer(self) -> str:\n        for entry in reversed(self.entries):\n            if entry.partial_answer:\n                return entry.partial_answer\n        return \"\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
