      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Controlling Scratchpad Verbosity"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A scratchpad that is too verbose consumes tokens without adding accuracy. A scratchpad that is too terse loses the reasoning trail. Tune verbosity with explicit prompt instructions:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CONCISE_SCRATCHPAD = \"\"\"\nBefore answering, write a brief scratchpad (3\u20135 lines maximum):\n- One line: what you need to find out.\n- One line per tool call you plan.\n- One line: your conclusion from the results.\nThen write <answer>...</answer>.\n\"\"\"\n\nDETAILED_SCRATCHPAD = \"\"\"\nBefore answering, use a detailed scratchpad:\n- Thought: break the problem into sub-questions (as many lines as needed).\n- Plan: list every tool call with its expected output.\n- Observation: after each tool call, record the result verbatim or summarised.\n- Reflection: what does the result tell you? Does it change your plan?\n- Partial answer: your best answer so far.\nRepeat Observation/Reflection until you have enough information.\nThen write <answer>...</answer>.\n\"\"\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Start with the concise format and switch to detailed only when you observe the model skipping steps or producing wrong answers \u2014 verbose scratchpads cost tokens on every call."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Logging and Debugging Scratchpads"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Capturing scratchpad text in a structured log is the fastest way to debug why an agent made a wrong decision:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
