          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import logging\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(\"agent.scratchpad\")\n\ndef log_scratchpad(\n    turn: int,\n    question: str,\n    scratchpad: str,\n    answer: str,\n) -> None:\n    logger.debug(json.dumps({\n        \"ts\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"turn\": turn,\n        \"question\": question[:120],\n        \"scratchpad_lines\": len(scratchpad.splitlines()),\n        \"scratchpad\": scratchpad[:500],\n        \"answer_preview\": answer[:120],\n    }, ensure_ascii=False))\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In production, route these logs to a structured store (Datadog, CloudWatch Logs, BigQuery) so you can filter by turn number, search for specific tool calls, and compare scratchpad reasoning across model versions."
