            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A scratchpad is the agent's private notepad \u2014 an area in the context buffer where the model thinks step by step before committing to an answer. Structuring the scratchpad with typed fields (Thought, Plan, Observation, Reflection) makes the reasoning legible and debuggable. The ReAct loop binds the scratchpad to tool use: each iteration writes a thought, calls a tool, records the observation, and either continues or produces a final answer. Persisting a condensed scratchpad across turns avoids re-deriving facts in long sessions, and logging every scratchpad turn is the most direct path to understanding and improving agent behaviour."
          }
        ]
      }
